1 SUMMARY
52 This bill directs the Department of Health and Human Services to establish, through
63 contracts with community entities, early childhood learning and development resource
74 hubs. The resource hubs must provide families with the information and support necessary
85 to locate early childhood programs; assist families in connecting with other resources in
96 the State; support the training of child care workers; and build networks among child care
107 providers. The bill requires the department, beginning January 1, 2027 and annually
118 thereafter, to submit a report to the joint standing committees of the Legislature having
129 jurisdiction over health and human services matters and education and cultural affairs and
1130 to the members of the Children's Cabinet and its advisory council regarding the status of
1141 state and regional early childhood education and family needs, data collected by resource
1152 hubs and any related recommendations to increase access to early childhood services. The
1163 bill provides $471,087 in funds in fiscal year 2025-26 and $1,621,048 in fiscal year
1174 2026-27 to support the purposes of the resource hubs.
